column6: Widespread small barnacles. Camera battery died unexpectedly and I was unable to shoot the “after” video this time, my apologies, John.
Heavy three-dimensional and hard-shelled animal growth was removed. Paint is at end of its useful life and is missing in large sections. Heavy slime attached to gel coat at waterline.
Many blisters have opened with marine growth taking root inside. Repair and repainting advised ASAP.
Widespread small blistering was observed on the hull, keel, and rudder
Heavy growth occurring above the waterline aft of the beam.
